      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i'm seeing some weird memory growth in our order processing module. i think i found a leak in this snippet but i'm not 100% sure why it isn't releasing the memory properly. can you take a look?\n\n```cpp\nvoid processOrder(int orderId, double price) {\n    Order* newOrder = new Order(orderId, price);\n    if (price <= 0) {\n        logError(\"Invalid price\");\n        return; \n    }\n    // ... processing logic ...\n    orderQueue.push(newOrder);\n}\n```\n\ncan u explain why this is leaking and how i should use a smart pointer here instead so it's safer?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
